text.section:
An applicant for cost-share assistance shall:
Submit a woodland management plan to the Department;
File an application with the Department stating:
The practice to be implemented;
The approximate cost of the practice to be implemented; and
A description of the land or lands upon which the practice is to be implemented;
File a statement of intent stating that the owner:
Intends to use the cost-share assistance for long-range timber growing and improvement; and
If there is joint tenancy, tenancy in common, or group ownership, has no knowledge of another application that is pending for cost-share assistance to be used on the land described in the application; and
Submit other information required by the Department.
